mainEntity.name: How long does it take to hike Camel's Hump?

acceptedAnswer.text: Most routes on Camel's Hump take 2-4 hours round trip. The most popular trail is 5.0 miles with Moderate difficulty. Start early, especially on weekends when parking fills quickly.

mainEntity.name: Is Camel's Hump hard to hike?

acceptedAnswer.text: Camel's Hump is rated Moderate. At 4,083 feet, expect challenging terrain above treeline with potential for rapid weather changes. Proper footwear and preparation are essential.

mainEntity.name: Do I need a permit to hike Camel's Hump?

acceptedAnswer.text: No hiking permit is required for Camel's Hump. However, parking fees may apply at trailheads (typically $3-5/day for WMNF or state parks). A WMNF parking pass covers most White Mountain trailheads.

mainEntity.name: When is the best time to hike Camel's Hump?

acceptedAnswer.text: The best hiking season for Camel's Hump is late May through October. Summer and fall offer the best conditions, though expect crowds on weekends. Winter hiking requires specialized gear and experience.

page_content.description:
At 4,083 feet, Camel's Hump ranks among New Hampshire's celebrated 4000-Footers—a collection of 48 peaks that challenge and inspire hikers throughout the Northeast. This moderate summit offers a quintessential White Mountain experience.

Popular Routes

The most popular route, **Burrows Trail**, covers 5.0 miles and is rated Moderate. Most popular route. Steady climb with excellent views.

Peak Bagging

This peak offers a standalone hiking experience with minimal nearby alternatives.

spring.title: Spring Conditions
spring.conditions: Muddy trails, snow above 3000ft until May
spring.tips: Trail closures for mud season (April-May). Check conditions before heading out.

summer.title: Summer Conditions
summer.tips: Start early to avoid afternoon storms and parking issues. Peak crowds on weekends.

fall.title: Fall Conditions
fall.conditions: Peak foliage late Sept, early snow possible in October
fall.tips: Peak foliage brings peak crowds. Weekday hikes recommended. Watch for ice above treeline in late October.

winter.title: Winter Conditions
winter.conditions: Full winter conditions, extreme cold and wind above treeline
winter.tips: Winter hiking requires specialized skills and gear. Never hike alone. Check avalanche conditions for steeper terrain.

current_hazards: ⚠️ ALPINE ZONE: Weather changes rapidly. Turn back if conditions deteriorate.
